<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-01-04</DATELINE><TITLE>Clostridium perfringens type A netF and netE positive and Clostridium difficile co-infection in two adult dogs</TITLE><BODY>The aim of this study was to report two cases of Clostridium perfringens type A and Clostridium difficile co-infection in adult dogs. Both animals were positive for A/B toxin. Toxigenic C. difficile and C. perfringens type A positive for NetE and NetF-encoding genes were isolated. This report reinforces the necessity of studying a possible synergism of C. difficile and C. perfringens in enteric disorders.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>